To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I request the following records from January 1, 2019 to present:

Records sufficient to show deaths investigated by the Coroner/Medical Examiner that occurred in:
group homes;
assisted living facilities;
board-and-care settings;
residential facilities for groups;
provider-operated community homes;
other community residential settings serving vulnerable adults or adults with disabilities.
For each such death, records sufficient to show:
date of death;
location/address;
facility/provider name if tracked;
manner of death;
cause of death;
whether toxicology was performed;
whether the death was referred to law enforcement or another agency.
Any logs, spreadsheets, or summary records sufficient to show annual totals of deaths investigated in such settings.
For any facility or address identified as having multiple deaths during the requested period, records sufficient to show the dates and causes/manners of death.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

David Cutie

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I request the following records from January 1, 2019 to present:

Records sufficient to show all referrals received from law enforcement, APS, HCQC, Nevada Medicaid, or the Nevada Attorney General concerning alleged abuse, neglect, exploitation, sexual abuse, battery, unlawful restraint, medication-related harm, or death in:
group homes;
assisted living settings;
board-and-care settings;
residential facilities for groups;
provider-operated community homes;
other community residential settings serving vulnerable adults or adults with disabilities.
Records sufficient to show, for each such referral if tracked:
date received;
referring agency;
general allegation type;
provider/facility name or address if releasable;
whether charges were filed;
whether prosecution was declined;
whether additional investigation was requested;
final disposition.
Any policies, manuals, charging guidance, or referral protocols concerning vulnerable-adult abuse or abuse in community residential settings.
Any aggregate reports or spreadsheets sufficient to show annual totals of referrals, charges, declinations, and dispositions involving abuse/neglect in such settings.

I am not requesting protected health information or unnecessary personal identifying information of alleged victims.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

David Cutie

